[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026665&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026665&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

The site requesting a zone transfer is the one who does the
checking of the serial numbers.  When trying to update a zone,
one should first request the SOA record.  If the new SOA's
serial number is greater than the current one, then a zone
transfer is requested.  It is the responsibility of the
authoritative nameserver (person) for the zone to update the
serial number when a change has been made.

Under UNIX systems, there are revision control systems that can
insert the version number into the file.  This can then be used
as the serial number.

				Kevin

